"To steer (steer) someone wrong" means to mislead someone, to take them to a place that they will not like, or to tell something to them that they won't like.
Gary says, "Would I steer you wrong?" meaning I will not steer you wrong; I will take you to somewhere that you will like.
Then he says, "Now let's get some grub."
"Grub" (grub) is an informal word for food.
